<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-85-0991 </DOCNO><TEXT>The population-inversion kinetics in high-pressure electron-beam-pumpedlasers using the 3p-3s transition of neon was investigated experimentally.Compositions of active media according to efficiency and specific poweroutput were determined in a wide range of specific pump powers. Optimalcharacteristics in the red spectral region were obtained at 724.5 nmin the case of excitation using an electron beam from a hot cathode;the efficiency was about 0.3 percent while the specific output powerwas about 1 W/cu cm. 21 references.</TEXT></DOC>